UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2586
1 A RESOLUTION recognizing May 2026 as Save Your Tooth Month in Kentucky.
2 WHEREAS, maintaining proper oral hygiene and preserving natural teeth are
3 essential for optimal oral health, which impacts patients' overall health and well-being;
4 and
5 WHEREAS, each year, over 25 million teeth are preserved through endodontic
6 treatments, including 15 million root canal procedures, emphasizing the importance of
7 saving natural teeth for improved appearance and maintaining essential functions such as
8 chewing and speech; and
9 WHEREAS, endodontists, as highly skilled dental specialists with two to three
10 additional years of training post dental school, utilize advanced technology and
11 specialized care to best treat tooth pain and infection; and
12 WHEREAS, endodontists excel in diagnosing and treating tooth pain and infection
13 through life-changing endodontic procedures, such as root canals, repairing traumatic
14 dental injuries, vital pulp therapy, and apicoectomy, thereby safeguarding patients'
15 natural teeth; and
16 WHEREAS, endodontists dedicate their dental practice exclusively to endodontic
17 treatments, performing an average of 25 root canal treatments weekly; and
18 WHEREAS, endodontists frequently collaborate with general dentists to ensure
19 comprehensive dental care and employ a specialized approach that leads to better health
20 outcomes and swift recovery for patients; and
21 WHEREAS, teeth serve as vital components for nutrition, emotional expression,
22 and overall health indicators, and neglecting oral hygiene can lead to various health
23 complications; and
24 WHEREAS, regular dental visits, thorough brushing and flossing twice daily, and
25 avoiding cavity-causing foods and habits are essential steps in maintaining gum, teeth,
26 and mouth health;
27 NOW, THEREFORE,
Page 1 of 2
